news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM tells GDA to expedite land acquisition for Harnandipuram Township
news.para: Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath has directed Ghaziabad Development Authority officials to speed up land acquisition for the Harnandipuram township. The project, funded by the state government, is progressing with over 35 hectares already registered. GDA now has enhanced powers to change land use, facilitating the development of the new city. The first phase targets 336 hectares from three villages.

news.title: Telangana government eyes ₹3,500 crore from Osman Nagar land auctions
news.para: Telangana government is auctioning approximately 48 acres of prime land in Osman Nagar, near Tellapur, aiming to raise ₹3,000-₹3,500 crore for welfare schemes. With an upset price of ₹39 crore per acre, these mixed-use plots are expected to attract significant developer interest due to their strategic location near the Financial District and Outer Ring Road.

news.title: Telangana Housing Board earns ₹34 crore from land auction in Hyderabad
news.para: Telangana Housing Board land parcels in Gachibowli and Kukatpally fetched high prices, reaching up to ₹1.76 lakh per square yard. The public auction on Monday saw 50 bidders compete for 14 land parcels, generating a total income of ₹34.27 crore for the board.

news.title: Ludhiana: 'Incomplete' Atal Apartment Scheme brochures leave people applying ‘blindly’
news.para: Ludhiana Improvement Trust's Atal Apartment Scheme faces controversy as applicants are issued forms without project brochures. Prospective buyers are reportedly applying "blindly" due to the non-availability of crucial terms, conditions, and technical specifications. LIT Chairman admitted brochures are being processed and promised availability by Monday.

news.title: Bombay HC raps government officer for cancelling redevelopment NOC after 10 floors built
news.para: Bombay High Court reprimanded a Mhada official for revoking a redevelopment No Objection Certificate (NOC) based on a representation, despite significant construction progress. Justices Kulkarni and Sathe emphasized that such drastic actions, usurping civil court powers, are illegal and infringe upon property rights. The court quashed the order, noting a concerning trend of bypassing legal recourse.

news.title: Online booking for 518 EWS flats in Nagpur under PMAY-Urban 2.0 starts on Feb 24
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation has launched online applications for 518 affordable housing units under PM Awas Yojana 2.0. The flats, available in 1 BHK and 2 BHK configurations, will be located at Mouza Nari. Registration opens February 24 and closes March 31, with allotment via a computerized lottery.

news.title: Coimbatore: 20% rise in steel prices likely to slow down construction activity
news.para: TMT steel prices have surged by 20% this month, increasing construction costs by approximately ₹50 per square foot. Builders are urging the government to establish a council to regulate raw material prices, citing significant profit margin impacts on small companies and potential project slowdowns.

news.title: Affinius‑led consortium to buy Veris Residential in $3.4 billion all‑cash deal
news.para: Affinius Capital and Vista Hill Partners have announced a definitive agreement to acquire Veris Residential in a transaction valued at approximately $3.4 billion. Under the terms of the deal, Veris shareholders will receive $19.00 in cash for each share they own.

news.title: Central government sanctions 2.88 lakh houses under PMAY-Urban 2.0
news.para: Over 2.88 lakh new homes have been approved under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana Urban 2.0. This brings the total sanctioned houses to more than 13.61 lakh. The approvals cover various categories including Beneficiary Led Construction and Affordable Rental Housing.

news.title: NBCC in discussion to secure 139-acre project in Seychelles
news.para: State-owned NBCC is exploring a major infrastructure project on a 139-acre island in Seychelles. The development will include housing, leisure facilities, and sports arenas. A high-level delegation from Seychelles visited NBCC's headquarters for detailed discussions. NBCC has a proven track record in similar projects, including in the Maldives.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust to pick 50% stake in Runwal Enterprises' upcoming mall in Mumbai for ₹434 crore
news.para: Nexus Select Trust  will acquire a 50 percent stake in a new mall in Mumbai. This deal is valued at Rs 434 crore. The upcoming mall is located in Dombivli. It will be operated in partnership with Runwal Enterprises. This acquisition is part of Nexus Select Trust's growth strategy.

news.title: Sunteck Realty strengthens sustainability credentials, scrores 78 in 2025 S&P Global ESG assessment
news.para: Sunteck Realty has achieved a remarkable score of 78 in the S&P Global Corporate Sustainability Assessment. This marks a significant improvement from its previous score. The company's commitment to sustainability is evident in its consistent year-on-year progress. Sunteck Realty also secured a 5-star rating and a score of 99 in the GRESB assessment.

news.title: Kerala completes five lakh houses under LIFE Mission: CM
news.para: Kerala's LDF government has achieved a significant milestone by completing five lakh houses under the LIFE Mission, aiming to eradicate homelessness. Launched in 2016, the project has seen an expenditure of over Rs 20,831 crore, providing substantial financial aid for house construction to families across the state.

news.title: Godrej Properties to jointly develop 18 acres land in Thane
news.para: Godrej Properties has secured an 18-acre land parcel in Thane for a new joint development. This large-scale residential project is expected to generate over ₹7,500 crore in revenue. The development marks GPL's fourth venture in Thane, promising a well-planned, integrated residential offering.

news.title: Gurugram: 450 shanties built on land along Golf Course Road razed
news.para: District authorities in Gurugram demolished approximately 450 shanties in Saraswati Kunj, Sector 53, on Saturday as part of an ongoing crackdown on unauthorized settlements. The operation, conducted on government land and internal roads, followed previous drives and prior notices, aiming to prevent further encroachment and protect public access.

news.title: Unity Small Finance Bank likely to foray into housing finance business next fiscal
news.para: Unity Small Finance Bank, after missing out on Aviom India Housing Finance, is prioritizing strategic options over aggressive acquisitions. The bank plans to enter the housing finance business in the latter half of the year, focusing on affordable housing and micro-LAP, while also preparing for a public listing in approximately two to two-and-a-half years.

news.title: DDA grants approval for change of use in land pooling area in north-west Delhi
news.para: Delhi Development Authority has approved the change of land use for Sector-8B, marking the first area eligible for development under the city's Land Pooling Policy. This milestone was achieved after Sector-8B met the mandatory 70% contiguous pooled land threshold, paving the way for integrated urban development.

news.title: Over 2,200 Bengaluru development body homes lie unsold
news.para: Thousands of Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) flats and villas on the city's outskirts remain unsold despite lower pricing than private developers. Poor infrastructure, including lack of road connectivity and civic amenities, along with maintenance issues, are deterring buyers. Despite sales incentives, demand is lukewarm, leaving many units vacant.
